body:
## What happened

Hello, thank you for reading.

When I was going to begin a new flutter demo this morning and clicked file -> new -> new flutter project, and this error occured. Yesterday it worked well, but this time it failed. 

I tried on another version `Android Studio 3.5.1`, and everthing is OK.

So maybe I should use the stable version ?

## Version information

Android Studio `4.0 Canary 1` • Flutter plugin `io.flutter 41.2.3` • Dart plugin `192.7761`

No Flutter sdk configured.

## Exception

null

comment_data.body: Thanks for the report. Unfortunately, due to technical issues in the distribution channel we cannot support the canary version of Android Studio 4 at this time. We're working on some infrastructure changes to allow it again, but it will take a while. We do support both stable and beta versions.
